cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper proposes a probabilistic model for inferring latent variables in the Hamming space from observed data. The model allows for simultaneous inference of the number of binary latent variables and their values, and preserves the neighborhood structure of the data. The paper also introduces a new application of dynamically extending hash codes. Based on these characteristics, the most likely sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM).
